Smarter machine design, ubiquitous surveillance and a firm justice
system would ensure that only a handful of "supercriminals" could
get away with it. The rest would either start to behave or go to jail
....which would mean that the cops could soon focus all their attention
on the few remaining bad guys, and deal with them. This effect would
be further enhanced by the legalization of victimless crime, which
means there would be a lot less criminals to begin with. It may sound
"statist" or "cynical" to some, but at least it would actually work. And,
last but not least, it would honor the rational principles of maximal
personal freedom and responsibility for one's actions.


