The concept of Arcology fits well with my current
pet theory of intelligence. My current theory
being that the majority of "intelligent" features
happen *between* brains rather than in them. In
this sense, Soleri's social "organisms" would be
the perfect way to create a more advanced society.
Certainly the idea that crowding can be a good
